<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496400>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. General morphology of Gymnodiscus. A. Habit of G. capillaris showing obovate–spathulate to oblanceolate basal leaves and capitula with 5 ray florets; B.habit of G. linearifolius showing the fusiform leaves and capitula with 8 or 9 ray florets." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496400/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496402>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Gymnodiscus capillaris.(A) flowering plant;(B1–B3) leaves;(C) involucral bract; (D) ray floret;(E) disc floret;(F) cypsela (ray floret); (G) ovary (disc floret); (H) style (disc floret); (I) anther; (J) detail of ovary hair showing twin cells; (K) pappus bristle. Voucher:Maguire 195, NBG.Scales: (A & B1–B3) 1 cm; (C–E) 1 mm; (F–K) 500 μm. Artist:S.L. Magoswana." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496402/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496404>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Distribution of G.capillaris." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496404/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

